Operator SingleChannelFilter


A SingleChannelFilter is an Operator which selectively blocks/passes MIDI
messages based on channel. Only a single channel may be selected at any time.
Separately non-channel messages my be blocked.   Use ChannelFilter for
multi-channel filtering.


Sub-Commands:

Command     op name, enable-system-events, bool
OSC         /pig/op name, enable-system-events, bool

Enables/disables filtering of MIDI system messages for named SingleChannelFilter

OSC Return: AKC

-----------------------------------------------------

Command     op name, q-system-events-enabled
OSC         /pig/op name, q-system-events-enabled

OSC Return: AKC bool false if MIDI system messages are filtered.
